Separate the construction of a complex object from its representation so that the same construction process can be used
to create different representations.

It encapsulates the construction of a Product & allows it to be constructed in steps.
Hides the internal representation of the product from the client.

Builder pattern also helps minimizing the number of parameters in constructor and
thus there is no need to pass in null for optional parameters to the constructor.

Object is always instantiated in a complete state rather than sitting in an incomplete state until the developer calls.